\b 7. 
\b0 ______ Dan talks about people who have inspired him along the way. Name 3-4 people who have been positive mentors for you. Could you contact them again and ask for their advice?\

\b 8. _____ Read Chapter Four
\b0 . Complete the Personal Checkup. Overview the 7 Areas for Achievement. Success typically does not \'93just happens.\'94 It shows up as a result of making deposits that are positive, healthy and success building. What are you doing in each of the seven areas that is building the success you want?\

\b 9. 
\b0 _____ Describe a time in your life when indecision caused you to lose an opportunity. You have now learned a simple 5-step process for removing the crippling effects of indecision. Think about any major decision you have ever made. How long did it take you to make that decision? Will you agree that indecision in any area cripples us in other areas of our lives? Can you agree that 48 Days is long enough to:\
1. Statetheproblem 2. Gettheadviceandopinionsofothers\
3. Listthealternatives 4. Choosethebestalternative 5. ACT\
Now complete the 
\i\b Countdown to the Work I Love 
\i0\b0 questions at the end of Chapter Four.\

\b 10.
\b0 _____ 
\b Read Chapter Five
\b0 . Recognize that \'93divine discontent\'94 is a good thing. It is likely God prompting you to take a fresh look at where you are and where you are going. Recognize that meaningful, purposeful work will integrate your:\

\f3 \'a5 \'a5 \'a5\

\f1 Skills & Abilities Personality Traits Values, Dreams & Passions\
The more you know about yourself in these three areas, the easier it will be to recognize work that fits you.\

\b 11.
\b0 _____ List your Personality Traits \'96\
Common personality traits are grouped into four categories:\

\b A. Dominance (Driver) \'96 Lion	-- Eagle\

\b0 Takes charge, likes power and authority, confident, very direct, bold, determined, competitive.\

\b B. Influencing (Expressive) \'96 Otter	-- Peacock\

\b0 Good talkers, outgoing, fun loving, impulsive, creative, energetic, optimistic, variety seeking, promoter.\

\b C. Steadiness (Amiable) \'96 Golden Retriever	-- Dove\

\b0 Loyal, good listener, calm, enjoys routine, sympathetic, patient, understanding, reliable, avoids conflict.\

\b D. Compliance (Analytical) \'96 Beaver	-- Owl\

\b0 Loves detail, very logical, diplomatic, factual, deliberate, controlled, inquisitive, predictable, resistant to change.\
Ask others to help you see yourself through their eyes.	Recognize that you are unique; there is no merit in being like everyone else.\

\b 12.
\b0 _____ List your Dreams & Passions -- What is it that you find naturally enjoyable? If money were not important, what would you spend your time doing? When do you find the time just flying by? What are those recurring themes that keep coming up in your thinking? What did you enjoy as a child but perhaps have been told was unrealistic or impractical to focus on as a career? You must include these in some form in your work \'96 otherwise it will be missing a critical element.\

\b 13.
\b0 _____ Be comfortable with this process of looking inward. Many people look outward too quickly and jump at what appears to be an opportunity only to discover\
six months down the road that it is not a fit. You are doing the important work now. 85% of the process of choosing the right career path comes as a result of looking inward. 15% is the application of what you then know about yourself in finding \'96 or creating \'96 work that fits. Now complete the 
\i\b Countdown to the Work I Love 
\i0\b0 questions at the end of Chapter Five.\

\b 14.
\b0 _____ Spend today believing that you were totally responsible for everything that has happened in your life so far. Just for today you can\'92t blame anyone for anything. If you accept responsibility for your losses, you will also put yourself in the driver\'92s seat for some big wins. Start imagining doing work that is fulfilling, meaningful and profitable \'96 every day from here forward.\

