\b 37. _____ Evaluate and Make Decisions. 
\b0 Ask for more information. Talk to people already working in prospective companies. Make any follow-up contacts from previous prospects where a decision had not been made. Remember, things change quickly and you have created \'93top of mind\'94 positioning with many companies. You can do a quick review of any possibilities that you stirred up.\

\b 38. ______ 
\b0 Write down 10 kinds of work you can think of where the person is paid for results rather then time. (For example \'96 and artist, a dentist, the guy who mows your yard, etc.) Does the idea of being paid for results scare you or does it sound attractive? You could pay a person laying blocks for your new porch $1 per block rather than an hourly wage. Or a graphic designer $75 for a new book cover design rather than $18 an hour. List kinds of work you would be willing to do based on results only.\

